        <p class="text-text-light text-sm mt-3">A paring disc pump within the disc centrifuge bowl converts the rotational momentum of the fluid into pressure, causing the liquid to discharge out of the bowl. Any restriction in the discharge passage of the liquids exerts pressure on the bowl — this externally created pressure is known as centrifuge backpressure.</p>
      </details>
